financial year ending on 31 December 2017.According to treasury, the adopted operating expenditure budget
amounts to R346.3 billion and R146.6 billion or 42.6% was spent by end of the
second quarter.Meanwhile, in that capital expenditure amounted to R20.6
billion, or 29.2%, of the approved capital budget of R70.6 billion.Treasury says the slow spending on the capital budget is a
concern.The report is part of the in-year Management, Monitoring and
Reporting System for Local Government (IYM), which enables provincial and
national government to exercise oversight over municipalities.